1. GNOME Terminal
2. Vim Bindings
3. Vim Plugins

1. GNOME Terminal:

(Change default terminal to GNOME)
gsettings set org.gnome.desktop.default-applications.terminal exec 'x-terminal-emulator'
sudo update-alternatives --config x-terminal-emulator
'then select GNOME as default'

(Tab creation/deletion)
Ctrl+Alt+n 'new tab'
Ctrl+Alt+k 'kill tab'

(Navigation)
Alt+j 'move to previous tab'
Alt+k 'move to next tab'
Alt+h 'move tab to the left'
Alt+l 'move tab to the right'
Alt+/ 'search'
Alt+n 'find next'

2. Vim Bindings:

(Tool)
fj 'auto indent the entire file'
Ctrl+n 'toggle NERDtree'

(Navigation)
ctrl+(hjkl) to 'switch around the Vims inside a same terminal'

3. Vim Plugins:

(Language)
Typescript: https://github.com/leafgarland/typescript-vim

(Tool)
YouCompleteMe: https://github.com/ycm-core/YouCompleteMe

(Navigation)
NERDTree: https://github.com/preservim/nerdtree
